# Figma QA And Completion

- This is the canonical completion and testing rule.
- Do not mark a Figma component complete after structure/layout validation alone.
- Do not mark work complete until both authoring-page acceptance and testing-page QA pass.
- Keep QA artifacts on testing pages, not authoring pages, and append new QA frames instead of replacing history.
- For tokenized components, require structural validation, screenshot validation, and semantic token validation before completion.
- For multi-mode work, require at least one screenshot of a live component instance in every required mode.
- For any component with variant axes, required QA must cover every intended variant combination unless preflight explicitly records a smaller approved matrix and explains why the omitted combinations are not part of the supported contract.
- Do not treat one representative instance as sufficient proof when the component exposes multiple variants, sizes, states, layouts, or other user-selectable axes.
- When the component also exposes `BOOLEAN`, `TEXT`, or `INSTANCE_SWAP` properties that materially affect usability, required QA must include the important property permutations called out in preflight, not only the default property state.
- Do not treat detached, manually restyled, or fallback artifacts as primary proof for mode correctness.
- If dark-mode readability depends on placeholder, secondary, tertiary, disabled text, or slot-backed visuals, verify those semantics on live instances before completion.
- If live-instance QA fails in any required mode, completion is blocked unless:
  - the issue is fixed, or
  - the unresolved surface is explicitly reported with preserved failing proof and a clearly labeled fallback artifact
- Before finishing, confirm:
  - authoring-page checks passed
  - testing-page QA exists for all required modes
  - every required variant combination was exercised on live instances in every required mode
  - every required non-default property permutation was exercised on live instances in every required mode
  - no mandatory QA step remains unresolved
